Require the Market Administrator to maintain a complete list of market stallholders and provide the Municipal Treasurer an updated copy on a regular basis; and

Assign additional personnel to the Treasurer’s Office who shall assist in the establishment and maintenance of computerized data.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require the:
Inventory Committee to conduct the inventory of the local roads under the jurisdiction of the Municipality and prepare the RPCLRN and furnish a copy thereof to the Auditor;
The Accounting Office and the GSO to prepare and maintain the required LRNLCs and LRNPCs for each local road and, thereafter, conduct regular reconciliation of the records;
The Engineering Office to provide the Accounting and the GSO with complete data relating to the description and cost segregation of road components for road projects; and
The Accounting Office to include the necessary disclosure on the total road network system in the Notes to the Financial Statements.

