Assign personnel who shall be in charge of securing the land titles of the subject lots, in coordination with the Accountant and the Property Officer;

Direct the Inventory Committee to conduct a complete physical inventory of its PPE including the real properties and report the same in the RPCPPE;

We recommended that Management:

Require the concerned Accountable Officer to submit the accounts and financial reports to the Treasurer and thereafter to submit to the Accounting Office all the disbursements vouchers and payrolls, official receipts, including the corresponding reports of each month on or before the  fifth day of the ensuing month or pursuant to the abovementioned pertinent provisions of laws, rules and regulations, as applicable;

Direct the Accountant to strictly comply with the timelines on the recording and submission of accounts to the Auditor, within the first ten (10) days of the ensuing month, as required by the abovementioned existing law, rules and regulations;

Look into the possibility of augmenting the Accountant’s Office of personnel from other departments, especially during report preparations and/or allowing them to render overtime, subject to availability of funds, in order to submit the accounts and financial reports on the mandated deadlines; and

Initiate the necessary administrative and/or criminal action in case of unjustified failure/refusal to effect compliance with the foregoing requirements by subordinate officials.

We recommended for the Municipal Government to:

Maintain its good practice of preparing a GAD Annual Accomplishment Report based on gender issues/GAD mandates under Plans and Budget that is approved by the Local Chief Executive;

Ensure through its GAD Focal Person that a duly reviewed and approved GAD Plan and Budget is in place as required in the PCW-DILG-DBM-NEDA JMC Nos. 2013-01 and 2014-01 prior to the incurrence of any GAD related expenditures to ascertain that these are valid and proper; and to ensure that the Budget and Plan was duly approved by PCW;

Direct the GAD Focal Person to strictly monitor the accomplishments by the concerned Department/Offices of the GAD P/P/As to ensure the implementation of the Annual GAD Plan, in order that the intended beneficiaries will be able to avail of its benefits or services.

